      "content": "\"Data access anomaly\" sounds a bit too much like we're admitting to a mistake. If we use that, a tech journalist is just gonna dig and find out it was a simple S3 misconfiguration mistake, which makes us look incompetent. \n\nIs there a way we can frame this so it sounds like it was part of a planned technical process or a routine system update? Something that doesn't imply anyone actually messed up the settings?",
